--- Page 1 ---
Patient Medical Record (Mock)
Patient Name: Johnathan Doe
DOB: 1981/04/12
MRN: 00482917
Medical History Entries:
1. Encounter Date: 2024/03/11
Visit Type: Primary Care – Annual Exam
Summary: Routine evaluation. BP slightly elevated (138/86). Lifestyle modification recommended. Basic labs ordered (CMP, CBC, Lipid Panel). Plan: Follow-up in 1 year unless symptoms change.
2. Encounter Date: 2024/07/02
Visit Type: Urgent Care – Respiratory
Summary: Patient presented with productive cough x7 days. CXR showed no consolidation. Dx: Acute
bronchitis. Medications Prescribed: Albuterol inhaler PRN, Azithromycin 5nday course. Plan: Rest, fluids, return if symptoms worsen.
3. Encounter Date: 2025/01/19
Visit Type: Dermatology
Summary: Evaluation of new mole on left shoulder. Dermoscopy benignnappearing, but photographed
for monitoring. Plan: Recheck in 6 months; return sooner if changes noted.
4. Encounter Date: 2025/03/05
Visit Type: Primary Care – Follown Up
Summary: BP improved to 126/79 after lifestyle adjustments. Labs normal. Plan: Continue regimen, next visit in 6 months.
5. Encounter Date: 2025/04/22
Visit Type: Orthopedics

--- Page 2 ---
Summary: Mild right knee pain after jogging. Xnray normal, suspected patellofemoral pain syndrome. Plan: Physical therapy referral, ice PRN.
